-- Real Estate firm Paramount Group files for IPO
-- 
-- Fri Oct 03, 2014 04:51PM EDT
-- None



Oct 2 (Reuters) - New York-based real estate company Paramount Group Inc filed with U.S. regulators to raise up to $2.65 billion in an initial public offering of common stock.

The company told the U.S Securities and Exchange Commission in a preliminary prospectus that BofA Merrill Lynch, Morgan Stanley and Wells Fargo Securities were underwriting the IPO. (http://bit.ly/1n0q6ld) The filing did not reveal how many shares the company planned to sell or their expected price.  The company intends to list its common stock on the New York Stock Exchange under the symbol "PGRE".